msgctxt "sn54.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 54 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 54 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Ekadhammavagga "
msgstr "1. One Thing "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 7. Mahākappinasutta → kappinasuttaṃ (bj) | kappino (pts1)
msgctxt "sn54.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Mahākappinasutta "
msgstr "7. About Mahākappina "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn54.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.7:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā mahākappino bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "Now, at that time Venerable Mahākappina was sitting not far from the Buddha cross-legged, with his body straight, and mindfulness established right there. "

msgctxt "sn54.7:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ mahākappinaṃ avidūre nisinnaṃ pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "The Buddha saw him, "

msgctxt "sn54.7:1.4"
msgid "Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.316, sc2
msgctxt "sn54.7:2.1"
msgid "“Passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etassa bhikkhuno kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā phanditattaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you see any motion or trembling in that mendicant’s body?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.7:2.2"
msgid "“Yadāpi mayaṃ, bhante, taṃ āyasmantaṃ passāma saṅghamajjhe vā nisinnaṃ ekaṃ vā raho nisinnaṃ, tadāpi mayaṃ tassa āyasmato na passāma kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā phanditattaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, whenever we see that mendicant meditating—whether in the middle of the Saṅgha or alone in private—we never see any motion or trembling in his body.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn54.7:3.1"
msgid "“Yassa, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, tassa so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samādhissa nikāmalābhī akicchalābhī akasiralābhī. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when an immersion has been developed and cultivated there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind. That mendicant gets such immersion when he wants, without trouble or difficulty. "

msgctxt "sn54.7:3.2"
msgid "Katamassa ca, bhikkhave, samādhissa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā? "
msgstr "And what is that immersion? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn54.7:4.1"
msgid "Ānāpānassatisamādhissa, bhikkhave, bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā. "
msgstr "When immersion due to mindfulness of breathing has been developed and cultivated there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind. "

msgctxt "sn54.7:4.2"
msgid "Kathaṃ bhāvite ca, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi kathaṃ bahulīkate neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā? "
msgstr "And how is immersion due to mindfulness of breathing developed and cultivated in such a way? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn54.7:5.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu araññagato vā rukkhamūlagato vā suññāgāragato vā nisīdati pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant—gone to a wilderness, or to the root of a tree, or to an empty hut—sits down cross-legged, with their body straight, and establishes their mindfulness right there. "

msgctxt "sn54.7:5.2"
msgid "So satova assasati, satova passasati … pe … "
msgstr "Just mindful, they breathe in. Mindful, they breathe out. … "

msgctxt "sn54.7:5.3"
msgid "‘paṭinissaggānupassī assasissāmī’ti sikkhati, ‘paṭinissaggānupassī passasissāmī’ti sikkhati. "
msgstr "They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe in observing letting go.’ They practice like this: ‘I’ll breathe out observing letting go.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn54.7:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ bhāvite ca kho, bhikkhave, ānāpānassatisamādhimhi evaṃ bahulīkate neva kāyassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā, na cittassa iñjitattaṃ vā hoti phanditattaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how immersion due to mindfulness of breathing is developed and cultivated so that there’s no motion or trembling of the body or mind.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn54.7:5.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

